        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-12-30T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-12-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="459" subtype="editorial-note"
                type="document" xml:id="d459">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>In a note to Soviet Chargé <persName corresp="#p_TSK1">Tsarapkin</persName> dated
                    August 29, 1947, replying to the Chargé’s note of August 18 (see editorial note,
                        <ref target="#pg_1039">page 1039</ref>), Acting Secretary of State <persName
                        corresp="#p_LRA1">Lovett</persName> reviewed the efforts of the United
                    States to reach agreements on matters affecting Germany as a whole and asserted
                    the intention of the United States to make arrangements with any other occupying
                    power willing to work for the achievement of the objectives already agreed upon
                    by the four occupying powers; for the text of the note, see <hi rend="italic"
                        >Germany 1947–1949</hi>, pages 362–363, Department of State <hi
                        rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, September 14, 1947, pages 530–531, and <hi
                        rend="italic">Documents on International Affairs, 1947–1948</hi>, pages
                    623–624.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
